translationAnswer.referenceTranslation: The Pearl River is a major river system in South China, flowing through Guangzhou, and is the third longest river in China, ranking only after the Yangtze River and the Yellow River. The Pearl River Delta (Delta) is one of the most developed regions in China, with an area of approximately 11,000 square kilometers. It is also one of the largest urban agglomerations in the world in terms of both area and population. The nine largest cities in the Pearl River Delta collectively house over 57 million people. Since China's reform and opening-up in the late 1970s, the Pearl River Delta has emerged as one of the major economic regions and manufacturing hubs in both China and the world.
